WEBVTT

00:01.664 --> 00:03.312
Hey. Remember what I told you.

00:03.337 --> 00:05.281
Next time you are on the top of the ***

00:05.297 --> 00:07.702
Make sure my boy ex
isn't at the bottom.

00:07.727 --> 00:09.350
- Mm-hmm.
- Heard that.

00:09.375 --> 00:11.695
All right, Simone here is
gonna take great care of you.

00:12.577 --> 00:14.878
- [MUMBLES]
- Sweet kid.

00:14.903 --> 00:16.170
Yeah.

00:16.195 --> 00:17.829
Hey, thanks for offering to help today.

00:17.854 --> 00:19.321
It's no problem.

00:19.346 --> 00:21.602
Though, I confess I may have
had an ulterior motive.

00:21.627 --> 00:22.560
Oh?

00:22.585 --> 00:24.937
Maggie's birthday, it's
in a couple weeks,

00:24.962 --> 00:27.029
and I'm stumped as far as gifts.

00:27.054 --> 00:29.288
Mmm. So what are you considering?

00:29.313 --> 00:32.348
Currently? Uh, thinking a
gold bracelet from Yurman.

00:32.372 --> 00:34.593
Jewelry, huh? That's a big statement.

00:34.618 --> 00:35.648
That's the thing.

00:35.673 --> 00:37.314
I'm not sure if we should
pick up where we left off,

00:37.339 --> 00:39.210
or play it like we're
starting from scratch.

00:39.235 --> 00:40.736
- Hm.
- [GUNSHOT]

00:40.826 --> 00:44.062
[GUNSHOTS, PEOPLE SCREAMING]

00:45.157 --> 00:47.039
There's someone hit on the corner.

00:47.064 --> 00:49.406
- Should we call it in?
- I'll administer aid.

00:49.431 --> 00:51.117
[PANTING]

00:51.346 --> 00:53.296
[CAR BEEPING]

00:53.321 --> 00:55.256
My chest! Bitch shot me in my chest!

00:55.281 --> 00:56.656
Hang on, we got you.

00:56.681 --> 00:58.093
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

00:58.118 --> 01:01.320
Gunshot wound, right
anterior lateral chest.

01:01.345 --> 01:02.712
All right, we're gonna roll him, okay?

01:02.736 --> 01:04.904
- Okay.
- [GRUNTS]

01:04.934 --> 01:06.187
Bullet went through and through.

01:06.212 --> 01:08.146
All right.

01:08.729 --> 01:11.890
<i>♪ </i>

01:13.372 --> 01:15.507
Decreased breath sounds on the right.

01:15.541 --> 01:16.937
His lung's collapsed.
Give me a needle, Barry.

01:16.962 --> 01:18.031
Got it.

01:18.126 --> 01:20.228
<i>♪ </i>

01:20.472 --> 01:21.992
Pulse is good.

01:22.754 --> 01:28.242
<i>♪ </i>

01:29.325 --> 01:31.304
Breath sounds improving.
Let's get him to Med.

01:31.329 --> 01:33.158
I'll go get the ambo.

01:33.183 --> 01:34.617
[ENGINE REVS, TIRES SCREECH]

01:34.642 --> 01:36.539
They're coming back. Get down!

01:36.564 --> 01:39.375
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS] Ow!

01:39.400 --> 01:40.875
[GUNSHOTS]

01:40.900 --> 01:43.535
[GLASS SHATTERS]

01:43.560 --> 01:45.528
- [GASPS]
- Ah! [GROANS]

01:45.553 --> 01:47.854
- [GASPS]
- [PANTING]

01:47.879 --> 01:49.746
[PANTING]

01:50.359 --> 01:54.195
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:54.767 --> 01:56.902
<i>[DOOR BEEPS]</i>

01:56.927 --> 01:58.392
Are you guys all right?

01:58.417 --> 01:59.687
Dispatch said you were in a shootout.

01:59.712 --> 02:01.289
What the hell happened out there?

02:01.314 --> 02:02.520
You're going to Baghdad.

02:02.545 --> 02:04.071
Tried to help this guy,

02:04.096 --> 02:06.464
banger circled back,
tried to finish the job.

02:06.489 --> 02:08.320
- Barry saved my life.
- What?

02:08.345 --> 02:10.580
Uh, 19-year-old male was
shot in the right chest.

02:10.604 --> 02:13.341
Needle decompressed in the
field, still hypotensive.

02:13.366 --> 02:14.781
Someone take a look at Barry's leg.

02:14.806 --> 02:16.149
- He was hit.
- Thanks, Barry.

02:16.174 --> 02:17.845
- Barry?
- Sorry, it's not serious.

02:17.870 --> 02:20.890
Uh, Noah, Dr. Sexton, meet
us in Treatment Four.

02:20.915 --> 02:22.593
On it.

02:23.217 --> 02:24.906
Kay, let's transfer on my count.

02:24.931 --> 02:26.551
Ready, one, two, three...

02:26.576 --> 02:28.143
[GRUNTS]

02:28.168 --> 02:29.935
Start on the groin line.

02:29.960 --> 02:32.915
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

02:32.940 --> 02:35.460
Open a 36 French chest tube.

02:35.687 --> 02:37.328
Hey, you still with me?

02:37.353 --> 02:39.388
Damn it. Hold the tube.

02:39.504 --> 02:41.523
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

02:41.781 --> 02:43.704
All right, just a tangential wound.

02:43.729 --> 02:46.342
Nothing to do but dress it
and let it heal on its own.

02:46.367 --> 02:48.070
Told you it wasn't
anything to worry about.

02:48.095 --> 02:49.529
Okay, tough guy.

02:49.554 --> 02:51.828
And why didn't you ever
tell me you carry a gun?

02:51.853 --> 02:54.210
- Maggie?
- Oh, hey, Alvin.

02:54.350 --> 02:56.117
Mr. Vaughn, I'm Detective Olinsky

02:56.142 --> 02:57.475
with the Chicago Police Department.

02:57.510 --> 02:58.953
Alvin, can this wait?
He's being treated.

02:58.978 --> 03:00.242
It's okay.

03:01.751 --> 03:03.718
Listen, we're gonna need your weapon.

03:03.743 --> 03:06.044
[GRUNTING] Course, yes, sir.

03:06.069 --> 03:08.687
It's locked in the glove
compartment of my rig.

03:08.712 --> 03:10.460
Uh, it's now evidence.

03:10.500 --> 03:12.406
Uh, you got a concealed carry permit?

03:12.431 --> 03:13.984
Yeah.

03:14.424 --> 03:16.125
There you go.

03:16.252 --> 03:17.648
You always got a gun at work?

03:17.702 --> 03:19.994
Uh, I've been carrying
for a couple years.

03:20.019 --> 03:21.119
Necessary precaution.

03:21.144 --> 03:22.429
And it's a good thing he does.

03:22.454 --> 03:23.854
He saved three lives today.

03:23.879 --> 03:26.180
For real. Barry, you the man.

03:26.604 --> 03:28.296
[BLOOD SPUTTERS]

03:28.321 --> 03:30.953
Big hemothorax. Lots of blood.

03:36.229 --> 03:38.030
Are you okay, Natalie?

03:38.055 --> 03:39.689
Yeah.

03:39.714 --> 03:41.548
[CLEARS THROAT]

03:41.846 --> 03:43.647
Tube's in. Securing it now.

03:43.672 --> 03:44.939
What's his pressure?

03:44.974 --> 03:47.834
107 over 68; heart rate of 121.

03:47.859 --> 03:50.565
Three units of blood,
one unit of plasma in.

03:50.590 --> 03:51.790
Okay.

03:51.815 --> 03:53.125
Color's coming back. He looks better.

03:53.150 --> 03:54.914
- Hey, Nat...
- Yeah?

03:54.939 --> 03:57.424
- We'll take over.
- Okay.

03:57.835 --> 04:03.978
<i>♪ </i>

04:04.203 --> 04:05.937
Just glad you're okay.

04:06.160 --> 04:08.779
[MUMBLING] Yeah. Yeah.

04:09.059 --> 04:10.860
Are you hurt anywhere? Let me see.

04:10.885 --> 04:12.830
No. No, I'm fine. I just, um...

04:12.855 --> 04:16.024
I hit my head when Barry
pushed me out of the way.

04:16.065 --> 04:17.995
If he hadn't...

04:18.764 --> 04:20.697
that bullet barely missed me.

04:20.723 --> 04:22.689
Yeah, well, thank God for Barry.

04:22.714 --> 04:24.064
But... but you, what...
what are you thinking,

04:24.089 --> 04:25.447
putting yourself in the
line of fire like that?

04:25.472 --> 04:27.754
Uh, I was thinking that there
was a patient in need.

04:27.779 --> 04:29.225
[DOOR OPENS]

04:29.250 --> 04:30.821
Dr. Manning, you feeling well enough

04:30.846 --> 04:31.885
to answer a few questions?

04:31.910 --> 04:34.823
Yeah, of course. [CLEARS THROAT]

04:34.848 --> 04:36.349
[ELEVATOR DINGING]

04:36.374 --> 04:39.544
- Right this way.
- Uh, is this really necessary?

04:39.569 --> 04:41.704
Like I said, it's probably indigestion.

04:41.729 --> 04:43.068
First thing they teach
you in med school:

04:43.093 --> 04:45.317
Always take chest pain seriously.

04:45.342 --> 04:47.773
That's what I get for hooking
up with a heart surgeon.

04:47.798 --> 04:49.232
[CHUCKLES]

04:49.328 --> 04:50.814
Here, why don't you pop
into this room right here,

04:50.839 --> 04:52.793
and I'll be in as soon as I can.

04:55.447 --> 04:57.148
Who'd you just plant in my room?

04:57.173 --> 04:58.077
She's a friend.

04:58.102 --> 05:00.005
Uh, she woke up this morning
with tightness in her chest.

05:00.030 --> 05:02.125
I'd like to get an EKG and troponins.

05:02.150 --> 05:04.755
- What's your friend's name?
- Margo...

05:05.468 --> 05:08.009
- Uh...
- Does she have a last name?

05:09.282 --> 05:11.387
Can you help me out here, Bea?

05:11.412 --> 05:13.180
Thank you.

05:20.093 --> 05:22.495
It must be hard remembering
all their names.

05:22.835 --> 05:24.267
Now, I read that Derek Jeter

05:24.292 --> 05:27.012
used to send his conquests
home with a gift basket,

05:27.209 --> 05:30.178
but a full cardio workup is...
is much classier.

05:30.203 --> 05:32.751
Jeter, huh? You... you're...
You're a baseball fan?

05:32.776 --> 05:35.639
No. It's too boring. But I love gossip.

05:39.198 --> 05:40.965
So you're in from Missouri?

05:41.000 --> 05:43.401
St. Louis. Here on business.

05:43.694 --> 05:45.996
Well, we will get you
in and out of here

05:46.030 --> 05:47.308
as quickly as possible.

05:47.333 --> 05:49.682
THAT'S WHAT DR. RHODES IS
RENOWNED FOR AROUND HERE:

05:49.716 --> 05:51.350
quick in-and-outs.

05:53.632 --> 05:55.186
I'm Dr. Bekker, by the way.

05:55.211 --> 05:57.079
Your insurance card has you listed

05:57.104 --> 05:59.423
as a dependent of Theodore J. Dimilio?

05:59.448 --> 06:01.188
That would be my husband.

06:02.118 --> 06:04.386
Would you like us to contact him?

06:04.420 --> 06:06.521
No, thank you. Not just yet.

06:06.555 --> 06:08.598
I'll make some copies
and be right back.

06:08.781 --> 06:11.890
<i>♪ </i>

06:12.431 --> 06:14.379
So you're married?

06:15.164 --> 06:17.223
Didn't wanna tell me?

06:17.767 --> 06:20.143
If I had, would you have
come back to my hotel room?

06:20.168 --> 06:21.535
No.

06:21.872 --> 06:24.451
<i>♪ </i>

06:24.568 --> 06:26.236
Maybe. I don't know.

06:26.261 --> 06:27.855
That's why I didn't tell you.

06:28.166 --> 06:29.507
<i>♪ </i>

06:29.779 --> 06:32.847
[DISTANT SIREN WAILING]

06:35.435 --> 06:36.869
Hey, there you are.

06:36.903 --> 06:38.209
I thought you were gonna come find me

06:38.234 --> 06:39.471
as soon as you were
done with the police.

06:39.496 --> 06:41.307
I just needed some fresh air.

06:41.543 --> 06:43.077
Well, I notified the ped's on-call.

06:43.102 --> 06:44.503
He's on his way in, so you can go home.

06:44.528 --> 06:46.329
What? Why?

06:46.467 --> 06:48.218
Thought you should take
the rest of the day off.

06:48.243 --> 06:49.701
Will, I'm fine.

06:49.726 --> 06:51.681
Just... please don't do that.

06:51.706 --> 06:54.236
Don't make unilateral
decisions on my behalf, okay?

06:54.261 --> 06:55.492
Excuse me!

06:55.517 --> 06:57.976
Excuse me, I need some help over here.

07:00.601 --> 07:02.362
[GROANING, SOBBING] Ow!

07:02.387 --> 07:04.639
She's been screaming blue
murder since Michigan City.

07:04.664 --> 07:07.305
I... I pulled over a couple of
times, so she could throw up.

07:07.330 --> 07:09.394
And she says it hurts too much to walk.

07:09.419 --> 07:11.761
[SOBBING] Ow!

07:13.116 --> 07:15.986
So you think I had a heart attack?

07:16.149 --> 07:17.849
I'm afraid so, yeah.

07:17.874 --> 07:19.474
Yeah, a mild one.

07:19.628 --> 07:22.877
Yeah, it's hard to tell exactly
what's going on from the EKG,

07:22.902 --> 07:24.711
so I wanna get you
over to the cath lab,

07:24.736 --> 07:28.071
so we can take a closer
look at your vessels.

07:28.688 --> 07:32.140
[CHUCKLES] I'm not gonna
catch my flight home, am I?

07:32.165 --> 07:33.666
No.

07:41.057 --> 07:42.672
Dr. Rhodes...

07:43.960 --> 07:45.702
I received a call from IR.

07:45.727 --> 07:47.628
Said you required a priority reschedule

07:47.663 --> 07:49.267
for your patient, Margo Dimilio?

07:49.318 --> 07:52.862
Yes. Uh, her EKG showed some PVC runs

07:52.887 --> 07:54.158
and possible ST changes.

07:54.183 --> 07:55.291
Ah.

07:55.316 --> 07:57.861
I'm not sure you heard, but
her lab work came back.

07:57.947 --> 08:00.828
They found traces of
cocaine in her urine.

08:01.599 --> 08:04.643
- What?
- 520 nanograms per milliliter.

08:04.668 --> 08:06.023
<i>♪ </i>

08:06.048 --> 08:08.908
I don't believe that's
what caused the distress.

08:08.988 --> 08:10.155
Why not?

08:10.385 --> 08:12.931
<i>♪ </i>

08:13.103 --> 08:15.608
All right, you want all the details?
Sure.

08:15.633 --> 08:19.289
Uh, we met at a fundraiser
at the Field Museum.

08:19.390 --> 08:21.291
Uh, we were at the roulette table.

08:21.316 --> 08:23.142
We both liked the number 19.

08:23.187 --> 08:25.744
She ends up inviting me
back to her hotel room,

08:25.769 --> 08:27.407
where we...

08:27.903 --> 08:30.659
exerted ourselves a couple of times.

08:30.684 --> 08:33.693
I only offer that up, because I believe

08:33.719 --> 08:35.821
it was the exertion

08:35.846 --> 08:38.614
that exacerbated the pain that
she was already experiencing,

08:38.639 --> 08:40.529
which is why I brought her in,

08:40.554 --> 08:42.726
and why I believe

08:42.751 --> 08:44.885
we need to take a closer
look at her vessels.

08:44.920 --> 08:46.040
Did you partake in the cocaine?

08:46.065 --> 08:47.432
No...

08:47.519 --> 08:49.219
and I didn't know that she was either.

08:49.244 --> 08:51.392
I can take a drug test if you'd like.

08:51.907 --> 08:53.608
That won't be necessary.

08:53.633 --> 08:54.881
Carry on.

08:55.272 --> 08:56.838
Thank you.

08:57.028 --> 08:58.906
<i>♪ </i>

08:59.310 --> 09:01.578
Let me know if anything makes
you feel uncomfortable, okay?

09:01.603 --> 09:03.537
- Yes, ma'am.
- All right, Mr. Cray...

09:03.572 --> 09:05.454
Uh, Reverend Cray, actually.

09:05.479 --> 09:07.309
Okay. Reverend, how old is Lindsay?

09:07.334 --> 09:09.568
14. Now, how long is this gonna take?

09:09.593 --> 09:10.471
And I'm only asking that,

09:10.496 --> 09:11.796
because we gotta get
down to Cedar Rapids.

09:11.821 --> 09:14.287
I'm preaching at a revival
meeting tomorrow.

09:14.312 --> 09:16.727
Okay, we'll just figure out
what's going on here first,

09:16.752 --> 09:17.673
and take it from there.

09:17.698 --> 09:19.425
Have you ever felt
pain like this before?

09:19.450 --> 09:21.537
Her last pregnancy, she'd
get sick like this,

09:21.579 --> 09:23.692
but n... not with all
this blood, you know.

09:23.717 --> 09:25.155
Last pregnancy?

09:26.065 --> 09:28.255
Lindsay, what happened
with your last pregnancy?

09:28.280 --> 09:30.313
- Did you carry to term?
- No, ma'am.

09:30.338 --> 09:33.650
She had what they called a
spontaneous miscarriage.

09:33.675 --> 09:35.843
- That was four months ago.
- [GASPING]

09:35.868 --> 09:37.635
Well, it doesn't look
like she's pregnant now.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.561
However, I am seeing
some irregularities

09:39.586 --> 09:41.287
in the lining of her uterus,

09:41.312 --> 09:42.514
perhaps something that
didn't move through

09:42.539 --> 09:43.993
when she had her miscarriage.

09:44.018 --> 09:45.428
All right, I'm gonna
do a pelvic exam now.

09:45.453 --> 09:47.338
Are you all right with that?

09:48.187 --> 09:50.289
You can come outside.
There's a waiting area.

09:50.314 --> 09:51.619
We'll give your daughter
a little more privacy.

09:51.644 --> 09:54.172
My daughter? Lindsay's my wife.

09:55.185 --> 10:02.425
<i>♪ </i>

10:08.365 --> 10:09.998
This marriage is legal?

10:10.032 --> 10:12.803
That guy and a 14-year-old girl?

10:12.828 --> 10:15.830
Her father gave his consent
and a judge signed off on it,

10:15.864 --> 10:17.974
- so yeah.
- What about her mother?

10:17.999 --> 10:19.915
Well, she died when
Lindsay was only three.

10:19.940 --> 10:23.050
- That man should be arrested.
- Right, but on what charges?

10:23.075 --> 10:25.601
Rape, coercion, whatever.

10:25.626 --> 10:26.896
This girl is a kid.

10:26.921 --> 10:28.770
She obviously had no
choice in the matter.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.162
He barely lets her speak.

10:30.187 --> 10:31.874
Can we call on the police?
Family services?

10:31.899 --> 10:34.067
No, unfortunately we're required to

10:34.092 --> 10:36.037
respect Michigan state law.

10:36.097 --> 10:37.831
How's the girl doing?

10:37.856 --> 10:39.145
She's undergoing a D&C

10:39.170 --> 10:41.265
to get rid of any products
from her prior miscarriage.

10:41.289 --> 10:43.021
Yeah, which the reverend only okayed,

10:43.046 --> 10:44.606
because he wants Lindsay
to be able to conceive

10:44.631 --> 10:46.099
as soon as possible.

10:46.124 --> 10:49.077
I realize this is
distasteful for all of us,

10:49.317 --> 10:52.038
but I implore both of
you to do your best

10:52.063 --> 10:54.028
not to let your personal feelings

10:54.169 --> 10:57.941
interfere with the care of
this patient or the law.

11:02.665 --> 11:04.032
What am I supposed to do?

11:04.057 --> 11:06.626
I'm not sure I can be in
the same room as that guy.

11:06.864 --> 11:08.431
Then go home. I'll deal with this.

11:08.521 --> 11:10.515
You keep trying to
push me out the door.

11:10.540 --> 11:12.575
Yes, I'm concerned about you.

11:13.047 --> 11:15.315
I don't know why you're
being so stubborn.

11:15.340 --> 11:18.141
I'm gonna go see how the D&C is going.

11:19.034 --> 11:21.769
[ELEVATOR DINGING]

11:23.534 --> 11:24.834
Dr. Reese!

11:24.859 --> 11:26.919
How did your rounds at
Cohn County Jail go?

11:26.944 --> 11:28.749
Great. Actually, the patient, Michael,

11:28.774 --> 11:31.109
who tried to kill his brother
in a bout of manic psychosis,

11:31.134 --> 11:32.704
we had a breakthrough this morning.

11:32.729 --> 11:34.013
He's no longer on suicide watch.

11:34.038 --> 11:36.727
Wow. Sounds like you're
really making some progress,

11:36.752 --> 11:39.343
not just with your patients, but, um...

11:39.368 --> 11:41.047
with your own therapy as well.

11:41.156 --> 11:43.156
I need to see a psychiatrist now!

11:43.181 --> 11:45.574
Don't listen to my husband.
Ben, you're being ridiculous.

11:45.599 --> 11:47.488
Sir, you need to wait for triage.

11:47.513 --> 11:49.015
Uh, it's okay, Leah.

11:49.201 --> 11:51.302
Hi, I'm Dr. Charles.
How can I help you?

11:51.327 --> 11:53.338
Listen, I need to check
myself into the psych ward.

11:53.363 --> 11:55.115
No, no, no, he doesn't. He's not crazy.

11:55.140 --> 11:56.877
Ben, please. People are listening.

11:56.902 --> 11:58.535
Do you think I care?

11:58.602 --> 11:59.992
I need to be committed

12:00.017 --> 12:02.185
for as long as it takes
to stop these thoughts.

12:02.210 --> 12:03.611
Okay, I understand.

12:03.636 --> 12:05.595
Um, how 'bout if we step
into this room over here,

12:05.620 --> 12:07.267
- so we can discuss your situa...
- No! No more talking!

12:07.292 --> 12:09.250
I don't need to talk. I
need to be locked up.

12:09.275 --> 12:10.450
- Ben...
- You send me back out of here,

12:10.475 --> 12:12.370
then I'm going to murder my wife.

12:12.586 --> 12:15.205
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

12:15.416 --> 12:19.353
<i>♪ </i>

12:19.636 --> 12:22.264
Wait, so, you're telling
me I need surgery?

12:22.289 --> 12:24.124
Unfortunately, yes.

12:24.247 --> 12:26.130
Uh, now, normally, we would
have placed a stent,

12:26.155 --> 12:28.164
but there's too much
curvature in the vessel.

12:28.189 --> 12:31.558
So, look, I recommend doing the
bypass as soon as possible.

12:31.583 --> 12:33.145
I can perform the operation myself.

12:33.170 --> 12:35.171
Uh, no, I... I... I need to get home.

12:35.196 --> 12:36.767
- Margo...
- This is all too much.

12:36.792 --> 12:38.224
I... I'm sure that there's
someone you can refer me to

12:38.249 --> 12:39.052
in Saint Louis.

12:39.077 --> 12:40.974
I... I'm very sorry, but
I can't let you leave.

12:41.163 --> 12:42.331
What?

12:42.356 --> 12:44.095
Your condition is too unstable,

12:44.120 --> 12:47.050
and we need to keep you under
observation until the surgery.

12:47.075 --> 12:48.942
I'm sorry, please, just...

12:48.967 --> 12:50.901
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

12:50.926 --> 12:52.275
Please.

12:52.440 --> 12:55.009
<i>♪ </i>

12:55.160 --> 12:56.694
What do they say?

12:56.719 --> 12:58.544
You reap what you sow?

12:58.889 --> 13:01.290
<i>♪ </i>

13:01.473 --> 13:04.378
This must be karmic retribution
for cheating on my husband.

13:04.600 --> 13:07.898
Your coronary disease didn't
just develop overnight.

13:08.518 --> 13:11.229
It's been building up for a long time.

13:11.652 --> 13:13.805
I've been cheating on my
husband for a long time.

13:14.444 --> 13:18.489
<i>♪ </i>

13:18.999 --> 13:20.185
Dr. Rhodes?

13:21.193 --> 13:22.411
Yeah.

13:22.516 --> 13:24.484
<i>♪ </i>

13:24.627 --> 13:27.207
I will let you know as soon as an O.R.
is open.

13:27.701 --> 13:34.774
<i>♪ </i>

13:37.209 --> 13:38.879
- She's agreed to a CABG?
- Mm-hmm.

13:38.904 --> 13:41.279
I'm confident we can do a
robotic assisted bypass.

13:41.304 --> 13:43.542
- It'll be less invasive.
- Of course.

13:44.253 --> 13:46.331
I'm having Dr. Bekker
perform the surgery.

13:46.356 --> 13:47.624
What?

13:47.649 --> 13:50.393
Uh, no, she is way less
experienced with the robotics.

13:50.418 --> 13:51.912
Hm, what happens if
something goes wrong?

13:51.937 --> 13:53.552
- Well, it won't.
- And if it does?

13:53.577 --> 13:55.344
Given the circumstances,
a lawyer could make

13:55.369 --> 13:56.536
a compelling case for negligence.

13:56.561 --> 13:57.599
No, Dr. Latham, I...

13:57.624 --> 14:00.319
There is too much potential
liability at stake

14:00.344 --> 14:01.444
for both you and the hospital

14:01.469 --> 14:03.490
to risk keeping you on the case.

14:04.441 --> 14:06.475
They're short a trauma
surgeon in the E.D.

14:06.500 --> 14:08.000
I volunteered you.

14:11.924 --> 14:13.458
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:13.483 --> 14:15.017
Hi.

14:15.042 --> 14:16.697
How are you feeling, Lindsay?

14:17.028 --> 14:19.649
A little groggy still,
but I feel better.

14:19.874 --> 14:22.776
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Is everything okay with her?

14:24.091 --> 14:26.607
Well, that's what I came in
to discuss with you both.

14:26.632 --> 14:28.020
Um...

14:28.045 --> 14:30.872
the gynecologist found a tumor
growing within the tissue

14:30.897 --> 14:33.167
that would've become the placenta.

14:34.026 --> 14:35.597
- Tumor?
- Yes.

14:35.622 --> 14:37.534
Um, she sent it to Pathology.

14:37.559 --> 14:39.527
It is, I'm afraid, malignant.

14:39.552 --> 14:41.668
It's called a choriocarcinoma.

14:42.562 --> 14:44.355
I have cancer?

14:45.165 --> 14:47.567
Thankfully, it's still
confined to your uterus.

14:47.592 --> 14:49.553
That's what's called Stage One.

14:49.687 --> 14:51.902
Given that we caught
it relatively early,

14:51.927 --> 14:55.864
these tumors generally
respond favorably

14:55.889 --> 14:57.523
to chemotherapy.

14:57.548 --> 15:00.522
And if that doesn't work,
what happens then?

15:00.547 --> 15:01.928
Worst-case scenario,

15:01.953 --> 15:04.083
we would need to
consider a hysterectomy.

15:04.108 --> 15:07.482
But we are far, far from
even discussing that.

15:07.507 --> 15:10.058
See? First she comes
in here, talks chemo.

15:10.083 --> 15:13.310
Next she's scheming to
remove your womb altogether.

15:13.335 --> 15:15.990
I can assure you, there
is no scheming going on.

15:16.015 --> 15:18.487
Chemo can lead to infertility.

15:18.512 --> 15:19.724
Not necessarily.

15:19.749 --> 15:21.883
Yes, there are some risk factors,

15:21.908 --> 15:25.077
but to do nothing at all
would be far, far riskier.

15:25.102 --> 15:26.091
No, thank you, then.

15:26.116 --> 15:28.609
We will not be doing any chemotherapy.

15:28.859 --> 15:30.226
Sir...

15:30.432 --> 15:32.294
I'm gonna ask you to
step out for a moment,

15:32.319 --> 15:34.614
so that I can discuss this
with my patient, privately.

15:34.639 --> 15:36.080
Why?

15:36.105 --> 15:38.242
She doesn't want me to leave.

15:38.970 --> 15:40.637
Go on, ask her.

15:40.946 --> 15:43.384
<i>♪ </i>

15:43.733 --> 15:45.334
He can stay.

15:45.580 --> 15:49.094
Like I said, only thing we
need from you now, Doctor,

15:49.119 --> 15:51.358
is to get Lindsay discharged.

15:52.012 --> 15:58.543
<i>♪ </i>

15:59.907 --> 16:02.003
Shortly after my wife got pregnant,

16:02.028 --> 16:03.958
I started having these thoughts.

16:05.833 --> 16:07.434
Okay, take your time.

16:07.625 --> 16:09.353
It's all right. No one
here's judging you.

16:09.378 --> 16:12.674
Um, I'd imagine... killing her,

16:12.699 --> 16:15.047
slashing her throat with
a knife, to be specific.

16:15.072 --> 16:17.255
I can't even be around knives anymore.

16:17.280 --> 16:18.856
Afraid of what I might do.

16:19.123 --> 16:20.805
That must be terrifying.

16:21.750 --> 16:24.291
Can I ask you, was this
pregnancy planned?

16:24.316 --> 16:26.792
Yes... no... we both wanted it.

16:26.817 --> 16:29.380
I don't... have an escape fantasy.

16:29.405 --> 16:32.287
I'm not jealous of my unborn child.

16:32.349 --> 16:34.331
It sounds like you've been
seeing some other therapists.

16:34.356 --> 16:35.558
[CHUCKLES] Two.

16:35.583 --> 16:37.290
One wouldn't even be
alone in a room with me.

16:37.405 --> 16:39.172
Thoughts only got worse after that.

16:39.308 --> 16:41.034
I'm really sorry you
had to go through hat.

16:41.408 --> 16:44.116
You know, sometimes when we over-focus

16:44.141 --> 16:45.980
on fixing problems like this,

16:46.005 --> 16:48.247
you know, not thinking
certain thoughts,

16:48.272 --> 16:50.073
it... it tends just to
tighten their grip.

16:50.131 --> 16:52.395
Like, if I tell you not
to think of a brown bear,

16:52.580 --> 16:54.083
you'd immediately picture it.

16:54.108 --> 16:56.543
Look, I'm telling you,
I'm in real danger.

16:56.568 --> 16:58.836
I need to be committed.

17:03.749 --> 17:06.300
Grabbed your spare
pants from your ambo.

17:07.059 --> 17:09.127
And found you this.

17:09.309 --> 17:10.843
- Mmm.
- Last one.

17:10.907 --> 17:13.412
Nearly had to wrestle Doris
to the ground for it.

17:13.436 --> 17:14.876
Thank you, babe.

17:15.621 --> 17:17.189
[GRUNTS]

17:17.377 --> 17:20.272
Uh, sit here for a second, would you?

17:26.482 --> 17:28.714
Something I've been wanting
to say since this morning.

17:28.739 --> 17:30.225
Me too.

17:30.501 --> 17:33.107
- But you go first.
- Okay.

17:34.466 --> 17:36.542
Getting back together with you,

17:37.703 --> 17:41.559
it is the happiest I've
been in a long time.

17:41.774 --> 17:43.907
Now, I know you had your
reservations about...

17:43.932 --> 17:46.302
Wait. [SIGHS] Wait...

17:46.378 --> 17:48.646
<i>♪ </i>

17:49.113 --> 17:51.481
When that call came through today...

17:51.784 --> 17:54.245
<i>♪ </i>

17:55.062 --> 17:56.913
I was so scared.

17:57.168 --> 17:58.897
I admit it's been hard for me

17:58.922 --> 18:00.672
accepting you back into my life,

18:02.013 --> 18:04.463
but I realize now that...

18:05.229 --> 18:07.176
what we have is real.

18:08.010 --> 18:10.337
Whatever happened in the
past, it doesn't matter.

18:10.686 --> 18:13.590
<i>♪ </i>

18:13.966 --> 18:15.741
I want a fresh start.

18:16.130 --> 18:20.541
<i>♪ </i>

18:20.718 --> 18:22.452
<i>[DEVICE BEEPING]</i>

18:22.713 --> 18:24.246
<i>♪ </i>

18:24.944 --> 18:26.917
[SIGHS]

18:27.671 --> 18:29.305
Continue this later?

18:29.936 --> 18:37.251
<i>♪ </i>

18:40.974 --> 18:42.241
[DOOR BEEPS]

18:42.275 --> 18:44.379
Miguel Garcia, 55-year-old male.

18:44.404 --> 18:46.439
Single GSW through the left clavicle.

18:46.473 --> 18:47.973
April, Dr. Choi, you're
going to Baghdad.

18:47.998 --> 18:49.932
- Copy.
- Hypotensive and unresponsive.

18:49.964 --> 18:51.265
Intubated in the field.

18:51.290 --> 18:52.578
My finger's in the bullet hole.

18:52.603 --> 18:53.870
I move it and blood
will hit the ceiling.

18:53.895 --> 18:56.314
- Keep pressure on it.
- All right.

18:56.638 --> 18:59.607
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

18:59.798 --> 19:01.599
<i>♪ </i>

19:01.624 --> 19:03.300
All right, set on my count.

19:03.325 --> 19:05.197
One, two, three...

19:05.222 --> 19:06.729
There we go.

19:06.754 --> 19:07.891
All right, it looks like

19:07.916 --> 19:10.253
the distal subclavian artery
through the clavicle.

19:10.278 --> 19:12.246
Let's take a look very carefully.

19:12.271 --> 19:13.294
[BLOOD SPUTTERS]

19:13.319 --> 19:15.201
Whoa! Okay, definitely the subclavian.

19:15.226 --> 19:17.068
All right. All right, here's the plan:

19:17.093 --> 19:18.652
April, give me the
biggest stitch needle

19:18.677 --> 19:20.630
- you can find, all right?
- Got it!

19:20.655 --> 19:22.486
Monique, you know where we
can find some zip ties?

19:22.511 --> 19:24.545
- Maintenance has them.
- Go get 'em quick.

19:24.570 --> 19:26.776
- Hey, Detective Olinsky?
- Yeah?

19:26.801 --> 19:29.130
Miguel Garcia, that victim
that we just brought in,

19:29.180 --> 19:31.605
shot-spotter pinpointed
the source of the gunfire

19:31.630 --> 19:34.927
to the same time and
location of your drive-by.

19:36.264 --> 19:44.086
<i>♪ </i>

19:48.434 --> 19:50.343
- Got zip ties.
- All right, good.

19:50.368 --> 19:51.745
All right, we're gonna
jerry-rig something

19:51.770 --> 19:52.818
to stop the bleeding.

19:52.843 --> 19:54.043
Ethan, I've got one hand.

19:54.068 --> 19:55.419
Get over here, grab the needle driver.

19:55.444 --> 19:57.035
- Got it prepped right here.
- Good.

19:57.194 --> 19:58.515
All right.

19:58.617 --> 20:00.949
Stick the needle through the
male end of the zip tie

20:00.974 --> 20:01.911
and tie a knot.

20:01.936 --> 20:03.513
April, hand me a scalpel.

20:03.667 --> 20:06.356
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

20:06.670 --> 20:10.223
<i>♪ </i>

20:10.776 --> 20:13.281
- Done. Here you go.
- All right.

20:13.409 --> 20:15.458
<i>♪ </i>

20:15.930 --> 20:17.849
All right, needle's in.

20:17.935 --> 20:20.269
Pull the stitch, and feed the zip tie

20:20.294 --> 20:22.608
around the clavicle and the artery.

20:22.787 --> 20:25.279
- Zip tie's in.
- All right, cinch it down.

20:25.375 --> 20:26.809
<i>♪ </i>

20:26.834 --> 20:28.802
- Gently.
- Mm-hmm.

20:29.322 --> 20:32.095
<i>♪ </i>

20:32.524 --> 20:34.364
All right.

20:34.754 --> 20:36.688
Okay, it's temporized.
How's the pressure?

20:36.713 --> 20:38.512
Holding. Heart rate's down.

20:38.537 --> 20:40.228
All right, let's get him up to the O.R.

20:40.789 --> 20:44.782
<i>♪ </i>

20:45.359 --> 20:47.025
What did they say his name was?

20:47.050 --> 20:48.204
Miguel.

20:48.356 --> 20:50.276
Don't go getting ahead of yourself.

20:50.687 --> 20:52.329
What if the bullet's mine, Maggie?

20:52.354 --> 20:53.654
What if it's not?

20:53.679 --> 20:55.763
Look, if anyone can
get him through this,

20:55.788 --> 20:57.381
it's Connor.

20:57.560 --> 20:59.454
Let's just stay in the moment for now.

21:00.219 --> 21:07.426
<i>♪ </i>

21:10.632 --> 21:12.633
Dr. Charles...

21:12.810 --> 21:14.144
You see he's overreacting, right?

21:14.169 --> 21:15.636
You're not going to commit him?

21:15.833 --> 21:17.544
I know it may be very
difficult to understand,

21:17.569 --> 21:20.961
but the thoughts your
husband is experiencing

21:21.176 --> 21:22.543
are very real to him.

21:22.568 --> 21:24.969
Look, you don't know my husband.

21:25.003 --> 21:26.934
We've been together since college.

21:26.959 --> 21:28.326
He's a gentle soul.

21:28.351 --> 21:30.186
But Ms. Samuels, your
husband's suffering.

21:30.342 --> 21:33.367
Don't we wanna try and help him
get some peace with all this?

21:33.392 --> 21:34.692
Of course.

21:34.727 --> 21:36.586
But if you commit him, then what?
I mean...

21:37.730 --> 21:40.461
Our baby needs his father.
Can't you just, um...

21:40.554 --> 21:42.270
give him some pills?

21:43.232 --> 21:45.437
There must be something you can do.

21:46.254 --> 21:49.059
Dr. Charles, can I speak
with you a moment?

21:49.403 --> 21:51.771
Would you excuse us for a second?

21:57.099 --> 21:59.501
It seems to me that Ben is suffering

21:59.526 --> 22:00.931
from some sort of OCD.

22:00.956 --> 22:03.031
Other than that, he has no
functional impairments.

22:03.056 --> 22:05.699
We're not talking about
over-washing your hands here

22:05.724 --> 22:07.589
or... or checking the front
door every two minutes.

22:07.614 --> 22:09.047
This is OCD Harm.

22:09.072 --> 22:10.839
His thoughts toward
his wife are violent.

22:10.864 --> 22:11.999
Judging from Ben's history,

22:12.024 --> 22:13.465
there's no reason to think
he would act on it.

22:13.490 --> 22:14.537
We don't know that.

22:14.562 --> 22:16.706
I mean, what if we send him
out here today and he does?

22:16.834 --> 22:18.468
Uh, I really think that...
that committing him

22:18.493 --> 22:19.365
is our best option.

22:19.390 --> 22:20.884
You know, put him in an environment

22:20.909 --> 22:22.276
where he feels safe from his thoughts,

22:22.301 --> 22:23.548
help him defuse them,

22:23.573 --> 22:25.416
or, at the very least,
coexist with them.

22:25.446 --> 22:26.367
What if the right move

22:26.392 --> 22:28.510
isn't to make him feel
safe from his thoughts?

22:28.535 --> 22:31.170
What if it's to make him
confront them directly?

22:31.269 --> 22:32.957
You mean exposure therapy?

22:33.284 --> 22:35.763
Dr. Reese, I know that's
been very helpful to you,

22:35.788 --> 22:38.200
but in this case, that approach
would be extremely risky

22:38.225 --> 22:39.901
and... and way too early.

22:39.926 --> 22:43.351
Look, we need time to fully
evaluate the patient, okay?

22:43.376 --> 22:45.244
So let's commit him to the psych ward

22:45.269 --> 22:47.737
and take it from there, okay?

22:51.303 --> 22:54.005
[ELEVATOR DINGING]

23:00.260 --> 23:02.142
- Dr. Rhodes?
- Not now.

23:02.167 --> 23:03.567
Has to be now.

23:03.682 --> 23:05.309
I'm ASA Ramirez, state's attorney

23:05.334 --> 23:07.080
investigating today's shootout.

23:07.254 --> 23:09.192
I'd appreciate if you could
retrieve the bullet,

23:09.217 --> 23:10.362
so that we could run ballistics.

23:10.387 --> 23:12.355
My priority is to save this man's life.

23:12.380 --> 23:14.874
You'll get your bullet if
it's medically advisable.

23:16.000 --> 23:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

23:26.228 --> 23:28.905
Uh, I'm not sure I should
be talking to you alone.

23:29.121 --> 23:30.851
Is that what he told you?

23:31.895 --> 23:33.972
Listen, I'm not sure

23:33.997 --> 23:35.964
how you feel about being married,

23:35.991 --> 23:37.925
but the one advantage
that it does give you

23:37.950 --> 23:40.372
is that you are considered, by law,

23:40.397 --> 23:42.476
to be medically emancipated.

23:43.990 --> 23:45.505
Emancipated?

23:45.530 --> 23:46.730
It means you have the right to make

23:46.755 --> 23:49.080
your own medical decisions.

23:50.013 --> 23:52.824
Does chemo really make it
so I can't have a baby?

23:53.364 --> 23:55.509
No. No.

23:55.534 --> 23:56.911
And Lindsay, it's clearly

23:56.936 --> 23:59.491
your best and safest
bet moving forward.

24:01.730 --> 24:03.316
What are you doing?

24:03.833 --> 24:05.199
It... n-nothing. No, we...

24:05.233 --> 24:07.601
I was just conferring with my patient.

24:07.636 --> 24:11.005
Lindsay, regardless of what
this man thinks or wants,

24:11.039 --> 24:12.339
it is your body and your choice...

24:12.374 --> 24:13.674
That has already been decided.

24:13.708 --> 24:15.480
Will you step outside with me, please?

24:15.505 --> 24:17.099
Sir, get your hands off of me!

24:17.124 --> 24:19.054
From the start, you have been
willful and argumentative.

24:19.079 --> 24:20.552
My patient has the right to decide

24:20.577 --> 24:22.334
how she wants to treat her cancer.

24:22.359 --> 24:23.392
The cancer is you.

24:23.417 --> 24:24.263
You've been treating Lindsay

24:24.288 --> 24:25.255
like she's a child, not a woman.

24:25.280 --> 24:27.515
She is a child! She's 14!

24:27.540 --> 24:29.216
Just because you had
some judge sign off

24:29.241 --> 24:30.169
on what's obviously a case of abuse...

24:30.194 --> 24:31.255
Excuse me... excuse me,

24:31.280 --> 24:33.008
I need to talk to someone
who's in charge here.

24:33.033 --> 24:35.543
And now you wanna play
games with her health?

24:35.568 --> 24:37.903
You are a bully and a predator!

24:37.928 --> 24:39.849
I'm the charge nurse here.
How can I help you?

24:39.874 --> 24:42.662
Yes, I want this bitch
removed from my wife's care.

24:42.869 --> 24:45.196
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

24:45.716 --> 24:51.354
<i>♪ </i>

24:51.396 --> 24:52.963
All right, we've got proximal

24:52.988 --> 24:54.941
and distal control of the artery.

24:55.418 --> 24:57.434
Need to remove the bone fragments

24:57.459 --> 24:59.861
before we can repair the vessel.

25:07.068 --> 25:08.368
Huh...

25:08.403 --> 25:10.971
It looks like the bullet
is kissing the vein.

25:11.005 --> 25:12.539
It's gotta come out.

25:22.969 --> 25:24.336
Behavior is what is outrageous.

25:24.361 --> 25:25.328
This is why I never
go to city hospitals.

25:25.353 --> 25:26.486
We will treat your wife...

25:26.511 --> 25:28.019
I heard he called you a bitch.

25:28.044 --> 25:30.311
Not really what matters here.

25:33.528 --> 25:36.050
Just got an earful from
the good reverend.

25:36.075 --> 25:37.519
If he takes Lindsay
out of this hospital,

25:37.544 --> 25:39.363
she will never get the
care that she needs.

25:39.388 --> 25:41.606
Every patient is allowed
a second opinion.

25:41.631 --> 25:44.700
But she'll die. It's
abuse, plain and simple.

25:44.725 --> 25:46.260
She's right.

25:46.754 --> 25:49.589
I admire your advocacy, Dr. Manning,

25:49.614 --> 25:51.211
but you're off the case.

25:51.273 --> 25:52.807
Dr. Halstead will be primary

25:52.832 --> 25:55.426
until the patient can be discharged.

25:56.175 --> 26:00.145
<i>♪ </i>

26:00.311 --> 26:01.552
I swear I have a mind

26:01.577 --> 26:02.662
to knock the hell out of
that sanctimonious...

26:02.687 --> 26:05.055
Will, I do not need my boyfriend

26:05.080 --> 26:06.465
to defend my honor right now, okay?

26:06.490 --> 26:09.043
What I need is for... ow.

26:09.068 --> 26:11.396
- [GROANS]
- Natalie, you all right?

26:11.421 --> 26:12.879
Yeah, I just...

26:12.904 --> 26:14.406
[GAGGING]

26:14.431 --> 26:15.853
Natalie...

26:15.878 --> 26:17.474
Natalie!

26:17.499 --> 26:20.243
- [PANTS]
- Nat...

26:23.606 --> 26:25.373
So you lost consciousness as well?

26:25.397 --> 26:26.770
Mm.

26:27.771 --> 26:29.936
Have you, uh, had
difficulty concentrating?

26:29.961 --> 26:31.928
I don't know, maybe.

26:31.953 --> 26:33.986
Have you been more
irritable than usual?

26:34.011 --> 26:35.442
Yes.

26:35.924 --> 26:37.458
Sorry, it's true.

26:37.483 --> 26:38.461
Look, I gotta get out of here.

26:38.486 --> 26:39.799
I have a patient I need to go see.

26:39.824 --> 26:41.057
Sorry, you don't get

26:41.082 --> 26:42.515
to go back in the game, Mitch Trubisky.

26:42.540 --> 26:43.711
You have a concussion.

26:43.736 --> 26:45.406
I'll need a head CT to
rule out any bleeds.

26:45.431 --> 26:47.232
Uh, let me make a call to Imaging.

26:47.257 --> 26:48.958
Thanks, Sam.

26:50.358 --> 26:53.118
I need to go talk to Lindsay
before she's discharged. Ow.

26:53.143 --> 26:54.810
- Natalie...
- What?

26:55.163 --> 26:57.088
Goodwin removed you from her care.

26:57.113 --> 26:59.669
- You don't remember that?
- She did?

27:00.833 --> 27:03.047
[SIGHS] Oh, no.

27:03.194 --> 27:07.161
[GROANS] I really messed this up, Will.

27:07.383 --> 27:09.451
- No, you didn't.
- Yes, I did.

27:09.476 --> 27:11.199
She was asking me about chemo.

27:11.224 --> 27:12.591
I... I was this close

27:12.616 --> 27:14.169
to convincing her to get treatment.

27:14.194 --> 27:16.363
If I had just had a
little longer with her...

27:17.118 --> 27:19.040
Well, maybe it's not too late.

27:20.918 --> 27:23.019
9 millimeter bullet.

27:23.509 --> 27:25.392
It was my gun.

27:26.186 --> 27:28.588
- I shot him.
- You can't blame yourself.

27:28.622 --> 27:31.618
You did what anyone in your
position would have done.

27:31.957 --> 27:34.546
- Mr. Vaughn?
- Yes?

27:34.854 --> 27:36.888
I need to ask you a few questions.

27:37.197 --> 27:44.270
<i>♪ </i>

27:45.542 --> 27:46.749
[SIGHS]

27:47.167 --> 27:50.107
- How are you holding up?
- [SIGHS]

27:50.132 --> 27:52.303
Trying to keep it together for him.

27:53.076 --> 27:56.011
To be honest, Ethan... I'm scared.

27:56.036 --> 27:57.546
Even if the worst happens,

27:57.571 --> 27:59.474
Barry's not criminally responsible.

27:59.499 --> 28:01.599
The shooting was instigated
by someone else.

28:01.624 --> 28:03.862
It was... it was self-defense.

28:03.887 --> 28:05.793
I know, but...

28:06.055 --> 28:08.823
how is Barry supposed
to carry that burden?

28:09.311 --> 28:17.272
<i>♪ </i>

28:18.342 --> 28:20.706
- It's inexcusable behavior.
- No, you're absolutely right.

28:20.731 --> 28:23.517
And again, I... I wanna apologize
for Dr. Manning's behavior.

28:23.542 --> 28:24.566
It was entirely unprofessional.

28:24.591 --> 28:27.493
Right, and very aggressive.
It was pushy.

28:27.518 --> 28:28.921
Yeah, well, between you and me,

28:28.946 --> 28:30.826
this is not the first time
we've had a problem with her.

28:30.851 --> 28:33.277
She can get emotional. Women, right?

28:33.302 --> 28:35.014
<i>[PHONE CHIRPS, BUZZES]</i>

28:35.039 --> 28:37.828
Ah, I have to check up on
a patient in Orthopedics.

28:37.853 --> 28:40.351
Let me... Monique, help
Reverend Cray here

28:40.376 --> 28:42.287
with, uh, discharge
paperwork, would ya?

28:42.312 --> 28:43.980
Patient's name is Lindsay Cray.

28:45.020 --> 28:46.749
Monique will take great care of you.

28:47.127 --> 28:49.010
Good luck and God bless, Reverend.

28:49.035 --> 28:50.856
I will be praying for
you and your wife.

28:50.881 --> 28:53.783
- Thank you.
- You're very welcome.

28:55.150 --> 28:57.619
[ELEVATOR DINGING]

29:01.832 --> 29:03.499
Where's the reverend?

29:03.533 --> 29:04.957
He's filling out the paperwork needed

29:04.982 --> 29:06.816
to take you out of here.

29:10.907 --> 29:13.042
I can't keep you here much longer.

29:13.076 --> 29:15.891
I know you have some
big decisions to make,

29:16.113 --> 29:18.414
but I won't be able to get you
the medical attention you need

29:18.448 --> 29:20.816
unless you speak up right now.

29:25.797 --> 29:29.218
My mother died when she was 19.

29:29.403 --> 29:31.080
She had ovarian cancer.

29:31.105 --> 29:32.952
My great-grandmother too.

29:33.586 --> 29:36.619
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Guess
it's the family curse.

29:36.871 --> 29:38.405
<i>♪ </i>

29:38.587 --> 29:40.221
I'm sorry to hear that.

29:40.246 --> 29:41.579
<i>♪ </i>

29:41.671 --> 29:43.557
The lady doctor said something earlier

29:43.582 --> 29:44.862
about a hysterectomy?

29:44.887 --> 29:46.507
Dr. Manning, yes.

29:46.532 --> 29:48.786
Now, that is only if you get sicker.

29:48.919 --> 29:50.219
With the right medicine,

29:50.244 --> 29:52.224
you have a great chance
of beating this.

29:52.249 --> 29:53.738
You can live a long life,

29:53.953 --> 29:55.642
have a family someday.

29:55.860 --> 29:56.960
<i>♪ </i>

29:57.414 --> 29:59.955
Are those things I'm
supposed to look forward to?

30:00.209 --> 30:02.722
<i>♪ </i>

30:03.131 --> 30:05.099
No, I want a hysterectomy.

30:05.282 --> 30:07.799
A hysterectomy is really not
necessary at this point.

30:07.824 --> 30:09.125
[SCOFFS] I don't care.

30:09.150 --> 30:10.690
Some women have their breasts removed

30:10.715 --> 30:12.009
if they have the cancer gene

30:12.034 --> 30:13.657
just so they don't get it later, right?

30:13.682 --> 30:15.401
But... but you are so young.

30:15.701 --> 30:18.369
All right, hysterectomy
is irreversible.

30:18.490 --> 30:20.418
You will not be able to become pregnant

30:20.443 --> 30:21.953
and have children, ever.

30:21.978 --> 30:24.446
You don't know my life, okay?

30:24.471 --> 30:27.036
You don't understand.

30:27.469 --> 30:30.671
[INHALES SHARPLY] I don't want
to bring a kid into this world.

30:30.886 --> 30:33.200
<i>♪ </i>

30:33.597 --> 30:35.932
Dr. Manning said it was my decision.

30:36.419 --> 30:43.492
<i>♪ </i>

30:45.165 --> 30:47.505
Mags, I just talked to Connor.

30:47.530 --> 30:49.471
They controlled the bleeding
and rebuilt the artery.

30:49.496 --> 30:51.813
We have every reason to believe
Miguel's gonna make it.

30:51.838 --> 30:54.306
[RELIEVED SIGH]

30:54.556 --> 30:56.724
We've gotta tell Barry.

30:57.598 --> 30:59.037
Barry?

30:59.995 --> 31:01.295
Barry?

31:01.320 --> 31:02.918
Why is he in handcuffs?

31:02.943 --> 31:04.677
The bystander made it out of surgery.

31:04.702 --> 31:06.136
Well, that's not the issue.

31:06.161 --> 31:08.463
There's some kinda discrepancy
with his carry permit.

31:08.488 --> 31:10.177
Permit? Come on, Detective.

31:10.202 --> 31:11.636
Barry, what's going on?

31:11.661 --> 31:13.962
I'm sorry, Maggie.

31:15.038 --> 31:21.794
<i>♪ </i>

31:22.990 --> 31:24.557
Have a seat, Ben.

31:24.686 --> 31:26.341
Wait, have I been committed already?

31:26.366 --> 31:27.785
Shouldn't I be medicated

31:27.810 --> 31:30.215
or in a straightjacket or something?

31:30.240 --> 31:33.018
So, the nurse is preparing
your admittance paperwork,

31:33.043 --> 31:34.466
but in the meantime,

31:34.491 --> 31:36.271
um, I would like to talk
to you about something.

31:36.296 --> 31:38.082
Talk about what? I already told you,

31:38.107 --> 31:39.719
I've done every type of
therapy in the book.

31:39.744 --> 31:42.269
- The thoughts won't go away.
- I understand.

31:42.294 --> 31:44.774
But what if I told you that

31:45.036 --> 31:47.505
most of the thoughts we
have are just nonsense?

31:47.530 --> 31:49.918
Just synapses popping off in our heads,

31:49.943 --> 31:52.741
and that we shouldn't
take them so seriously?

31:54.914 --> 31:57.015
If you could, just...

31:57.040 --> 31:59.079
do me a favor for a moment...

31:59.104 --> 32:01.172
and close your eyes.

32:06.009 --> 32:08.578
Now, I want you

32:08.603 --> 32:12.436
to bring up the thought that
frightens you the most.

32:12.962 --> 32:15.096
Tell me what you see.

32:17.336 --> 32:20.071
It's okay. You are in a safe space.

32:21.872 --> 32:24.674
<i>[SOFT MUSIC]</i>

32:25.310 --> 32:26.840
I see myself...

32:28.253 --> 32:31.055
- I'm holding a knife.
- Okay, keep going.

32:31.080 --> 32:32.989
<i>[APPREHENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

32:33.014 --> 32:34.448
I see my wife.

32:34.535 --> 32:36.755
She's in the kitchen, doing dishes.

32:36.851 --> 32:38.751
<i>♪ </i>

32:38.776 --> 32:40.844
I'm walking up behind her.

32:40.869 --> 32:43.074
She doesn't know I'm there.

32:43.762 --> 32:45.527
You're doing very well.

32:45.884 --> 32:49.134
<i>♪ </i>

32:49.732 --> 32:51.215
What's that?

32:51.476 --> 32:53.757
<i>♪ </i>

32:54.107 --> 32:57.076
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

32:57.314 --> 33:00.583
<i>♪ </i>

33:00.608 --> 33:02.558
I paged Dr. Charles. Let me
know when he comes up here.

33:02.583 --> 33:03.769
- Kayla...
- Oh, here he is.

33:03.794 --> 33:05.355
- I got your page. What's up?
- It's Dr. Reese.

33:05.380 --> 33:07.172
She's locked in with a patient.

33:07.686 --> 33:14.959
<i>♪ </i>

33:21.939 --> 33:24.608
[EXHALES SOFTLY, SHAKILY]

33:25.135 --> 33:30.706
<i>♪ </i>

33:32.817 --> 33:36.018
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

33:36.053 --> 33:38.359
<i>You've conquered</i> th or shower
<i>your fear of holding a knife...</i>

33:38.384 --> 33:39.963
a weapon.

33:41.124 --> 33:43.216
Now, imagine that I'm your wife.

33:43.493 --> 33:46.261
<i>♪ </i>

33:46.530 --> 33:48.130
I can't.

33:48.155 --> 33:49.599
You can.

33:49.763 --> 33:51.430
I trust you.

33:51.747 --> 33:53.671
<i>♪ </i>

33:53.696 --> 33:56.627
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- Do you see her?

33:56.652 --> 33:58.358
Yes.

33:58.859 --> 34:00.804
Here's your opportunity.

34:00.842 --> 34:03.444
You can slit my throat right now.

34:03.947 --> 34:11.187
<i>♪ </i>

34:27.824 --> 34:29.418
No.

34:29.443 --> 34:30.971
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

34:30.996 --> 34:33.155
No, I don't want to.

34:34.460 --> 34:37.161
- I don't wanna do it.
- No, you don't.

34:37.187 --> 34:38.197
This whole time,

34:38.222 --> 34:40.366
you've been beating yourself
up over your thoughts.

34:40.391 --> 34:42.175
The fact that you can't dismiss them

34:42.199 --> 34:44.400
- does not mean you're depraved.
- [SCOFFS SOMBERLY]

34:44.437 --> 34:45.837
<i>♪ </i>

34:45.980 --> 34:48.138
It shows you have a conscience.

34:48.293 --> 34:50.527
<i>♪ </i>

34:50.734 --> 34:53.540
[SOBBING]

34:54.210 --> 34:56.178
Dr. Reese...

34:56.437 --> 34:58.905
outside now.

34:59.035 --> 35:01.685
<i>♪ </i>

35:03.360 --> 35:05.450
Dr. Charles, I know I didn't
take your approach today...

35:05.475 --> 35:07.077
You didn't take my approach?

35:07.102 --> 35:08.802
You directly defied my orders,

35:08.827 --> 35:11.729
and put yourself and your
patient in real danger.

35:11.763 --> 35:14.398
Ben isn't dangerous. I
think I just proved that.

35:14.433 --> 35:15.436
The only thing you proved to me

35:15.461 --> 35:16.780
is that you're reckless
and insubordinate,

35:16.805 --> 35:18.499
and I have half a mind
to suspend you again.

35:18.524 --> 35:20.414
The last few months, you've
been preaching to me

35:20.439 --> 35:21.586
that I can either see my patients

35:21.611 --> 35:23.145
as a threat or as an opportunity.

35:23.170 --> 35:25.138
Was I afraid in there? Yes.

35:25.163 --> 35:26.797
But my fear no longer controls me.

35:26.822 --> 35:28.535
I control it, and now
Ben controls his too.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.017
You are missing the point!

35:31.581 --> 35:33.748
I appreciate that exposure therapy

35:33.773 --> 35:35.540
has given you a newfound
sense of confidence,

35:35.565 --> 35:39.281
but it does not make you
all-knowing and invincible.

35:39.725 --> 35:43.194
What you just did in there
was unbelievably stupid.

35:43.713 --> 35:50.986
<i>♪ </i>

35:51.461 --> 35:53.462
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:53.574 --> 35:55.287
Sharon? You called for me?

35:55.320 --> 35:57.022
- Yeah.
- [DOOR CLOSES]

35:57.191 --> 35:58.897
Sit down with me for a minute.

35:58.922 --> 36:02.388
What is it? Do I need to get
Barry a lawyer? A bondsman?

36:02.413 --> 36:05.860
I just spoke with my guy at the
State's Attorney's office,

36:05.885 --> 36:09.354
the discrepancy with
Barry's carry permit.

36:09.379 --> 36:12.414
- Yeah?
- It turns out...

36:12.439 --> 36:15.091
he changed his identity at some point,

36:15.116 --> 36:17.151
because of a juvenile record.

36:17.261 --> 36:20.263
He didn't disclose it on his permit.

36:20.462 --> 36:23.730
That's why it wasn't technically legal.

36:23.758 --> 36:26.359
What do you mean change his identity?

36:26.384 --> 36:28.326
You mean Barry Vaughn...

36:28.419 --> 36:30.353
isn't his real name?

36:30.465 --> 36:32.667
Apparently not.

36:32.692 --> 36:35.961
<i>♪ </i>

36:36.215 --> 36:37.983
Why wouldn't he tell me?

36:38.008 --> 36:39.375
<i>♪ </i>

36:39.400 --> 36:41.167
He had a whole other life?

36:41.192 --> 36:42.993
<i>♪ </i>

36:43.018 --> 36:45.620
I'm sorry, Maggie.

36:45.714 --> 36:49.717
The State's Attorney is gonna
file a charge against him.

36:49.742 --> 36:51.209
<i>♪ </i>

36:51.234 --> 36:53.235
The whole time we were together...

36:53.260 --> 36:55.027
<i>♪ </i>

36:55.052 --> 36:56.620
He was lying?

36:56.645 --> 36:59.547
<i>♪ </i>

36:59.572 --> 37:01.473
Every day?

37:01.498 --> 37:04.266
[WHIMPERING]

37:04.291 --> 37:06.581
<i>♪ </i>

37:06.655 --> 37:08.049
Every day, Sharon.

37:08.723 --> 37:15.996
<i>♪ </i>

37:19.256 --> 37:21.257
What is going on here?

37:21.292 --> 37:23.746
Lindsay has decided to
have a hysterectomy.

37:23.771 --> 37:25.839
Over my dead body.

37:25.864 --> 37:28.485
She's my wife. I make the decisions.

37:28.510 --> 37:29.677
Sir, please move.

37:29.702 --> 37:31.323
You lay so much as a finger on her,

37:31.348 --> 37:34.006
and I will sue you to kingdom come.

37:34.031 --> 37:35.865
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

37:36.085 --> 37:37.653
We have her consent.

37:37.875 --> 37:41.429
<i>♪ </i>

37:41.868 --> 37:44.091
You lied to me.

37:44.233 --> 37:46.656
She can't make that kind
of decision for herself.

37:46.681 --> 37:48.119
She was obviously coerced.

37:48.144 --> 37:50.429
He... he forced you to
sign this, didn't he?

37:51.277 --> 37:54.576
No. It was my decision.

37:55.260 --> 38:00.703
<i>♪ </i>

38:01.862 --> 38:04.253
You have two seconds to
step aside, Mr. Cray,

38:04.278 --> 38:07.062
or I will have you forcibly
removed from the premises.

38:07.397 --> 38:14.577
<i>♪ </i>

38:14.761 --> 38:16.364
You... you go through
with this, Lindsay,

38:16.389 --> 38:18.668
and you will be banished by the church,

38:18.693 --> 38:20.402
the community, everything.

38:20.427 --> 38:24.016
You will be diminished
in the eyes of the Lord.

38:24.423 --> 38:26.258
Do you understand?

38:27.097 --> 38:30.733
<i>♪ </i>

38:34.647 --> 38:36.483
Surgery went without a hitch.

38:37.240 --> 38:41.054
Seems your personal life
keeps working in my favor.

38:44.092 --> 38:45.926
Excuse me, Dr. Bekker?

38:45.951 --> 38:47.597
I'm Teddy Dimilio.

38:49.053 --> 38:51.746
I just wanted to thank you
for saving my wife's life.

38:51.953 --> 38:54.021
It was actually Dr. Rhodes here

38:54.046 --> 38:55.946
who made the diagnosis.

38:55.971 --> 38:58.839
Well, both of you then.

38:58.864 --> 39:01.132
Yeah. [GRUNTS]

39:01.157 --> 39:03.558
I don't know what I
would've done without her.

39:06.116 --> 39:08.017
It was our pleasure.

39:08.042 --> 39:09.809
Thank you.

39:11.990 --> 39:13.991
<i>[SOFT MUSIC]</i>

39:14.016 --> 39:15.984
[DOOR CLOSES]

39:16.269 --> 39:21.907
<i>♪ </i>

39:21.932 --> 39:23.599
[DOOR CLOSES]

39:23.624 --> 39:26.893
<i>♪ </i>

39:26.918 --> 39:29.019
[SIGHS]

39:29.044 --> 39:32.146
<i>♪ </i>

39:32.171 --> 39:34.205
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

39:34.230 --> 39:35.697
- Hey.
- Hey.

39:35.722 --> 39:38.690
Someone told me about a
standoff between you and Cray?

39:38.870 --> 39:40.037
Yeah.

39:40.062 --> 39:41.829
Were you able to talk to Lindsay?

39:41.854 --> 39:44.168
- I was.
- Is she gonna start chemo?

39:45.076 --> 39:47.243
She's having a hysterectomy.

39:47.457 --> 39:49.678
I tried to talk her out
of it, believe me,

39:49.703 --> 39:51.537
but she was adamant.

39:52.039 --> 39:55.804
It's a drastic step to take,
but I can see why she took it.

39:56.017 --> 39:58.169
That girl will finally have her say.

39:58.264 --> 40:00.933
- But she's just a kid, Nat.
- She's tough.

40:01.499 --> 40:03.233
Women are tough,

40:03.258 --> 40:05.084
tougher than you think.

40:05.885 --> 40:08.337
I guess I got a lot to learn
about this kinda stuff.

40:08.362 --> 40:09.996
[CHUCKLES]

40:10.021 --> 40:14.491
Trust me, you are way
further along than most.

40:14.731 --> 40:16.365
<i>♪ </i>

40:16.399 --> 40:18.670
- Way, huh?
- Mm-hmm. [LAUGHS]

40:18.695 --> 40:20.228
All right.

40:20.849 --> 40:27.922
<i>♪ </i>

40:28.052 --> 40:30.587
Thank you.

40:30.612 --> 40:32.580
[MUMBLES]

40:32.605 --> 40:35.574
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

40:36.212 --> 40:43.251
<i>♪ </i>

40:48.909 --> 40:50.977
Impressive save today.

40:51.002 --> 40:52.636
Yeah, thanks.

40:52.661 --> 40:54.462
You headed somewhere?

40:54.487 --> 40:58.223
No, just headed home.
It's been a long day.

40:58.248 --> 40:59.982
Shame.

41:00.007 --> 41:02.442
Waste of a nice tux.

41:02.467 --> 41:03.834
I know a spot over in the West Loop.

41:03.859 --> 41:06.093
Makes the best Old Fashioned's in town.

41:06.118 --> 41:08.185
Care to decompress over a drink?

41:08.217 --> 41:12.487
<i>♪ </i>

41:12.512 --> 41:14.752
You're not married, are you?

41:14.777 --> 41:16.114
No.

41:16.643 --> 41:18.110
<i>♪ </i>

41:18.683 --> 41:20.649
In that case, I'm more of
a Manhattan kinda guy,

41:20.674 --> 41:22.685
but I might be able to be persuaded.

41:22.710 --> 41:24.745
<i>♪ </i>

41:24.770 --> 41:27.038
- Car's right here.
- All right.

